\t\t\t<a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/2011/02/broccoli-shells-n-cheese/#comment-71504\">01.11.13 at 5:33 pm</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-content\">\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<p>KLC &#8211; A good way to tell is the color.  It&#8217;s technically a white sauce, so you don&#8217;t want the roux to get dark, but watch for just the slightest turn towards tan.  The color will start to change as the flour toasts.  Usually its good in a minute or two, but the time will fluctuate with small differences in the amount of heat under the pot.  It&#8217;s kind of one of those things that you just need to get the hang of :)</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2011/02/broccoli-shells-n-cheese/?replytocom=71504#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm(\"comment-71504\", \"71504\", \"respond\", \"13351\")'>Reply</a>\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\n\t<li class=\"comment even thread-even depth-1\" id=\"comment-80476\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-header\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-author vcard\">\n\t\t\t\t<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/62430fad8ee8b28a5438a2a6a1653158?s=48&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />\t\t\t\t<cite class=\"fn\">Tricia</cite> <span class=\"says\">says:</span>\t\t \t</div>\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-meta commentmetadata\">\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/2011/02/broccoli-shells-n-cheese/#comment-80476\">05.21.13 at 9:51 am</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-content\">\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<p>I&#8217;m thinking of turning this into a cheesey rice recipe. I&#8217;ll start by cutting the sauce in half so it doesn&#8217;t drown the rice. Do you think that would work and if so, any ideas as to what type of rice would work best?</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a class=